      <h1 id="opal-compiler">Opal Compiler</h1>
<p>The OpalCompiler is a Smalltalk-to-Bytecode compiler for Pharo. Originaly it was named NewCompiler.</p>

<ul>
<li>Support for full block closures.</li>
  <li>Easy to understand and modify.</li>
  <li>Based on the AST of the Refactoring Engine.</li>
  <li>Retargable Backend</li>
</ul><p>I was one of the initial developer of bytecode generator. 
Here is a presentation about OpalCompiler on DeepIntoPharo: <a href="http://de.slideshare.net/jressia/opal-compiler">link</a></p>

<p>OpalCompiler is now integrate into Pharo 3.0</p>

<p>Now Opal Compiler is maintain by Marcus Denkers et Bera Clement.</p>
    </div>
	
